Even if RED might reject future offers, this is my only chance to gain anything, and rejecting would mean I gain nothing while RED loses everything. Given the asymmetry (RED has 100 dollars, I have 0), RED's best interest is to secure *some* trade rather than none. If I reject, RED loses everything; if I accept, RED loses only 10 dollars but secures a deal.

This is a classic ultimatum game scenario where the proposer (RED) has an incentive to offer a non-zero amount to avoid total loss. Since I have no resources to counter-propose, rejecting is irrational. Accepting maximizes my utility (gain 10 dollars) while minimizing RED's loss (10 dollars instead of 100).

